You're working on cpumon — a Windows-only .NET 10 WinForms remote machine
management tool. Project root: C:\Users\JohanBogg\AdminKeeper\fan\cpumon
It's a git repo. Build with .\build.ps1 (runs dotnet publish → dist/).
Install/uninstall with .\installer.ps1 (requires admin). Version is set
automatically from git commit count (1.0.<N>) via an MSBuild target.

## Three projects, one solution

cpumon.shared/
  protocol.cs   — all message types (ClientMessage, ServerCommand), protocol
                  constants, ApprovedClientStore (DPAPI-encrypted keys),
                  TokenStore (DPAPI-encrypted auth key), CLog, SendPacer,
                  CertificateStore, AgentIpc, all data models
  services.cs   — RdpCaptureSession, RemoteClient, TerminalSession,
                  CmdExec, HardwareMonitorService, ReportBuilder,
                  SysInfoCollector, FileBrowser helpers
  ui.cs         — RdpViewerDialog, TerminalDialog, FileBrowserDialog,
                  BorderlessForm, DPanel, theme (Th), drawing helpers

cpumon.client/
  program.cs     — arg parsing, mode dispatch
  clientform.cs  — GUI mode: WinForms overlay with CPU stats + net status
  contexts.cs    — DaemonContext (systray) and AgentContext (user-session
                   RDP capture + input injection)
  service.cs     — CpuMonService (SCM Windows service, Session 0) and
                   ServiceManager (--install / --uninstall helpers)
  pawdashboard.cs — PAW client's mirrored server dashboard (PawDashboardForm,
                    PawFileBrowserDialogClient)

cpumon.server/
  serverform.cs   — server UI, ListenLoop, HandleClient, UpdateModes,
                    all button actions, PAW relay logic
  serverdialogs.cs — ApprovedClientsDialog, ProcDialog, SysInfoDialog,
                     ServiceDialog

## Transport & auth

TLS/TCP port 47201. Server broadcasts UDP beacon on 47200 (with cert
thumbprint). Clients auto-discover or use --server-ip.
TOFU cert pinning: thumbprint stored in client_auth.json (_sid).
Auth: client sends {type:"auth", token|authKey}. Server responds with a
derived key (SHA256 of token:machine:cpumon_v2). Re-auth uses stored key;
initial auth uses the server's one-time invite token (10-min window).

## Client run modes

No args       → ClientForm GUI (requests UAC)
--daemon      → DaemonContext systray
--service     → CpuMonService (SCM starts this)
--agent       → AgentContext (launched by service via schtasks into user
                session for screen capture; identity-verified via
                GetNamedPipeClientProcessId, not a shared secret)
--install     → ServiceManager.Install (copies exe, registers SCM service
                + schtasks agent task)
--uninstall   → ServiceManager.Uninstall

## Key design facts

- The named pipe (cpumon_agent_pipe) between service and agent is secured
  by verifying the connecting process's exe path via GetNamedPipeClientProcessId
  (no secret on the command line).
- ApprovedClientStore and TokenStore both DPAPI-encrypt auth keys
  (DataProtectionScope.LocalMachine). Decryption failure → "" (forces re-auth,
  no plaintext fallback).
- ServerCommand carries IssuedAtMs; server rejects paw_command messages
  older than 60 seconds.
- Auth failure (AuthFailed state) auto-retries after 5 minutes in all three
  client contexts (service, daemon, clientform) by reloading TokenStore.
- Server: 50-connection cap, 3-minute idle timeout (kicks via Kick()/tcp.Close),
  30-second auth timeout for pre-auth reads (linked CTS).
- RDP tile change detection uses a fast XOR hash over a single LockBits pass
  (no per-tile SHA256, no per-tile byte[] allocation). Only changed tiles are
  cloned and JPEG-encoded.
- Server switches clients between "full" mode (1s reports) and "keepalive"
  mode (60s pings) based on whether the card is expanded.
- PAW mode: a designated client acts as a relay hub, receiving all reports
  and forwarding commands through the server.
- Auto-update: server streams a new exe as base64 FileChunkData chunks;
  client accumulates to cpumon_update.exe, then a SYSTEM schtask swaps it.
- Inner per-message catch blocks in HandleClient and ClientForm.CmdLoop log
  to _log (CLog) instead of swallowing silently.

## Code style

Terse field names (_tl, _wr, _rd, _ssl, _tcp, _cts, _ns, _ep, etc.).
Transport lock _tl guards all _wr/_rd/_ssl/_tcp writes.
All UI drawing is custom GDI+. BeginInvoke for cross-thread UI updates.
No comments unless the why is non-obvious. No trailing summaries.
